---
title: Spring Greens Gnocchi with Asparagus, Peas, and a Creamy Tarragon Sauce
description: Asparagus and peas are two sure signs that spring is here. The veggies are synonymous with the season—some even say they’re sweeter and more tender at this time of year. We couldn’t resist tucking them into this gnocchi, which features a tarragon cream sauce that’s just light enough to really let those gorgeous greens shine.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w13-r9-042f6cbc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w13-r9-0db3063d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spring-greens-gnocchi-589cc7a2043c3c78d63a2754
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 830 mg
time required: 25 minutes
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of @salted water{(for boiling)} to a boil. Trim and discard bottom inch from @asparagus{6%ounce}(trimmed and cut into 1-inch pieces), then cut stalks into 1-inch pieces. Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}(thinly sliced). Pick leaves from @tarragon{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked and finely chopped) and finely chop.

Once water is boiling, add @gnocchi{9%ounce} to #pot. Cook until tender and floating, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove with a #slotted spoon and set aside in a #medium bowl. Add asparagus to pot cook until bright green, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reserve ¼ cup cooking water, then drain.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-low heat. Keep over heat until it begins to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and toss in garlic. Using residual heat, cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @peas{4%ounce} and toss to coat in butter.

Add gnocchi and asparagus to pan and toss to combine. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Return pan to stove over medium heat. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, half the @walnuts{1%ounce}(half), and half the tarragon. Continue stirring until everything is heated through and a creamy sauce has formed, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If sauce seems thick, add a splash of cooking water to loosen.

Divide gnocchi mixture between plates. Garnish with remaining walnuts and tarragon and serve.